# /root/.asoundrc — installed by deploy/install.sh with
# __DONGLE_CARD__ substituted by the detected USB-C dongle name.
#
# Why this file exists:
#   - jasper-voice's TTS needs a path to the speakers that's separate
#     from the CamillaDSP music chain. Without a shared destination,
#     TTS would have to either go through the loopback (mixing with
#     music in unhelpful ways) or directly to the dongle (locked
#     while CamillaDSP holds it).
#   - dmix (`jasper_out`) is that shared destination: CamillaDSP's
#     processed music + jasper-voice's TTS both write here; dmix sums
#     them sample-wise; one stream goes to the dongle.
#
# Topology:
#
#   renderers (librespot, shairport-sync, bluealsa-aplay)
#     → hw:Loopback,0,0  (snd-aloop playback)
#                   │
#                   ▼ (loop)
#         hw:Loopback,1,0  (snd-aloop capture)
#                   │
#                   ▼ (plughw, rate-converts)
#               jasper-camilla (CamillaDSP)
#                   │
#                   ▼ (writes to dmix below)
#         pcm.jasper_out  ─── dmix ───┐
#                                     │
#         jasper-voice TTS  ──────────┤  (also writes to dmix)
#                                     │
#                                     ▼
#                            hw:CARD=__DONGLE_CARD__,DEV=0
#                                  Apple USB-C dongle → speakers
#
# When the AEC bridge is enabled (see CLAUDE.md "Acoustic echo
# cancellation"), the `pcm.jasper_capture` dsnoop tap below lets
# CamillaDSP and the AEC bridge share the loopback capture side as
# multiple readers. dsnoop is the multi-reader-safe ALSA primitive
# (the dual of dmix on the playback side). The dsnoop slave is
# configured for 48 kHz S16_LE stereo — the rate the bridge and
# CamillaDSP both target internally.
#
# RATE LOCK FOOTGUN (snd-aloop is first-opener-wins): per the ALSA
# wiki on Matrix:Module-aloop, the Loopback device takes its stream
# parameters from the first process that opens it. If shairport-sync
# opens hw:Loopback,0,0 directly at its native 44.1 kHz S32
# (since 2026-05-11's PR #75, which removed the plughw resample
# upstream), the loopback locks at 44.1 kHz until everyone closes
# it. Subsequent dsnoop opens at 48 kHz then fall back to the
# locked rate — readers that don't tolerate that get distorted or
# silent audio.
#
# Two readers, two access paths:
#   - CamillaDSP opens `plug:jasper_capture` (note the `plug:`) in
#     v1.yml. plug auto-converts rate/format, so camilla is rate-
#     tolerant: works whether the loopback is 44.1 or 48.
#   - AEC bridge opens `jasper_ref` (defined below) — a plug-wrapped
#     alias of jasper_capture. Mirrors the same pattern. The bridge
#     gets samples at whatever rate it requests via alsaaudio,
#     regardless of the loopback's actual locked rate.
#
# Why two names: keeps `pcm.jasper_capture` semantically "the raw
# dsnoop tap" so other consumers / diagnostics see exactly what
# the kernel produced, while `pcm.jasper_ref` advertises its
# intent ("AEC reference, rate-agnostic") at the call site.
#
# We never want camilla to read `hw:Loopback,1,0` directly — that
# would deny dsnoop the slave, and the bridge would fail to open
# with `unable to open slave`.

pcm.jasper_capture {
    type dsnoop
    ipc_key 7778
    ipc_perm 0666
    slave {
        pcm "hw:Loopback,1,0"
        rate 48000
        channels 2
        format S16_LE
        period_size 1024
        buffer_size 4096
    }
    bindings {
        0 0
        1 1
    }
}

# Plug-wrapped alias for the AEC bridge's reference capture.
#
# `plug` transparently resamples whatever the dsnoop delivers to
# whatever the bridge opens with. The bridge opens at 48 kHz S16_LE
# (per REF_RATE in jasper/cli/aec_bridge.py); plug converts from
# the dsnoop's actual delivered rate (typically 44.1 kHz today due
# to shairport native, sometimes 48 kHz with Spotify Connect) to
# the requested 48 kHz. CPU cost is sub-1% of a Pi 5 core at S16
# stereo / speech rates; latency cost is a few ms of buffer.
#
# Without this wrapper, the bridge would receive distorted or
# silent samples when the loopback's locked rate ≠ 48 kHz —
# the root cause of the AEC-broken-with-AirPlay regression
# diagnosed on 2026-05-15.
pcm.jasper_ref {
    type plug
    slave.pcm "jasper_capture"
}

ctl.jasper_capture {
    type hw
    card Loopback
}

pcm.jasper_out {
    type dmix
    ipc_key 7777
    ipc_perm 0666
    slave {
        pcm "hw:CARD=__DONGLE_CARD__,DEV=0"
        rate 48000
        channels 2
        format S16_LE
        period_size 1024
        buffer_size 4096
    }
    bindings {
        0 0
        1 1
    }
}

ctl.jasper_out {
    type hw
    card __DONGLE_CARD__
}
